Former Garsen MP Danson Mungatana wants ODM leader Raila Odinga to stop forcing rebels to remain in the party.He said the rebels are fed up with being in the losing end and want to be part of the government to benefit directly. Raila cannot force people to remain in the opposition, Mungatana said.He spoke during a fundraiser for 10 madrassas. Mungatana addressed Bondeni residents in Mikinduni ward, Galole constituency, Tana River county.He asked Raila to state what he has done to Kenyans, instead of politicking.The former Kenya Airports Authority chairman has declared he will run for Tana River governor.